byline.original: By NICHOLAS CASEY and WILLIAM NEUMAN

abstract: Venezuelan lawmakers swear in three legislators who had been prevented from taking their seats by Supreme Court in December 2015, setting up confrontation with president's Socialist party.

headline.print_headline: The Americas; Venezuela: New Lawmakers Defy Supreme Court
headline.main: Venezuela: New Lawmakers Defy Supreme Court

snippet: The lawmakers swore in three three legislators who were blocked from taking their seats by the court last month.
lead_paragraph: The lawmakers swore in three three legislators who were blocked from taking their seats by the court last month.
